article.headline: Alcorn St. 80, Alabama St. 77
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. (AP) -- Juan Wyatt and Alex Owumi each scored 17 points to lead Alcorn State to an 80-77 overtime win over Alabama State on Monday night. The score was tied 72-all at the end of regulation, but the Braves (6-13, 4-3 Southwestern Athletic Conference) outscored the Hornets (5-13, 3-2 SWAC) 8-5 in overtime. Delvin Thompson added 12 points for Alcorn State, and Clifton Douglass had 11. Alabama State's Andrew Hayles had a game-high 18 points. Joel Bosh and Dustin Richmond added 13 and 10 points, respectively. The Braves shot 54.9 percent from the floor, compared to 36.5 percent by the Hornets.
